accessibility.text: Olympus Mons, a large shield volcano on Mars, stands over 21.9 km (13.6 mi) high, about 2.5 times the elevation of Mount Everest. It is the tallest volcano on Mars and, along with Rheasilvia on Vesta, the tallest mountain in the Solar System. Located in the Tharsis Montes region, Olympus Mons last erupted 25 million years ago.
